### Step 2: variable labels in one place

`label_map()` returns the current variable-to-label mapping as a two-column
(`key`, `label`) data frame. Holding labels in one place is what keeps an axis
title in a figure and a column header in a table reading the same way. Change a
label here and it propagates everywhere the map is read, so you never hand-edit
"Ejection Fraction" in five places and miss the sixth.


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
lm <- label_map(dat)
gt(head(lm, 10))
```

